00:35:59.660 --> 00:36:03.550
Regret Theory is a
theory that --

00:36:03.550 --> 00:36:07.450
it's kind of related to
Kahneman and Tversky.

00:36:07.450 --> 00:36:11.180
It says that people fear
the pain of regret.

00:36:11.180 --> 00:36:12.620
There's an old expression.

00:36:12.620 --> 00:36:14.500
"I was kicking myself,"
because I

00:36:14.500 --> 00:36:16.750
made some bad decision.

00:36:16.750 --> 00:36:19.760
Well, that's a painful
experience when you did

00:36:19.760 --> 00:36:21.710
something wrong.

00:36:21.710 --> 00:36:25.680
This is represented somewhat
in the kink in the Prospect

00:36:25.680 --> 00:36:27.700
Theory value function.

00:36:27.700 --> 00:36:30.050
But Regret Theory says that
there's actually a painful

00:36:30.050 --> 00:36:32.810
emotion, that you're
wired not to like

00:36:32.810 --> 00:36:34.460
to have made a mistake.

00:36:34.460 --> 00:36:37.200
And so then, you end up
designing your life around

00:36:37.200 --> 00:36:39.880
that and trying to avoid
doing anything that you

00:36:39.880 --> 00:36:41.450
might regret later.

00:36:41.450 --> 00:36:46.480
And it can create problems. You
may make bad decisions,

00:36:46.480 --> 00:36:51.310
because you're overly worried
about regret.

00:36:51.310 --> 00:36:52.560
Gambling behavior.

